examples: The moccasin maker had a pile of deerskin on the table, waiting to be cut out.
Nichole wore a pair of deerskin gloves because she said she could feel more through them.

definitions.definition: The hide, whether tanned or not, of one deer.
examples: The hunter exchanged twenty deerskins for a bottle of whiskey at the trading post.

definitions.definition: An article of clothing manufactured from deerskin. Often constructed in the plural.
examples: The trapper wore deerskins because they were softer than cow leather garments and rustled less than canvas.

main_definition: ( uncountable ) Leather made from deer hide .
secondary_definitions: ( countable ) The hide, whether tanned or not, of one deer.
( countable ) An article of clothing manufactured from deerskin. Often constructed in the plural.
